10. Purpose of Cloning a Virtual Machine
The purpose of cloning a virtual machine is to create an exact copy of an existing VM, which is useful for:
Rapid deployment of identical environments
Backup and disaster recovery
Testing configurations without affecting the original VM
Scaling applications horizontally
